Description: RNH_ECOLI - Also known as dasF, herA, rnh, sdrA. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Endonuclease that specifically degrades the RNA of RNA-DNA hybrids. RNase H participates in DNA replication; it helps to specify the origin of genomic replication by suppressing initiation at origins other than the oriC locus; along with the 5'-3' exonuclease of pol1, it removes RNA primers from the Okazaki fragments of lagging strand synthesis; and it defines the origin of replication for ColE1-type plasmids by specific cleavage of an RNA preprimer. From Escherichia coli (strain K12).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
